      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LEWIE KELLY (10) hit his peak and gave his opponents no chance when he cruised to a 14 metre victory over an in-form rival at Newcastle last week. May need a bit of luck from this draw but that latest effort is good enough to take out a race like this. WHITBYS DELIGHT NZ (11) should find this easier than last Saturday's attempt at Menangle. Not drawn the best so may need a 10/10 drive but scored from a wide barrier two back at Newcastle and hasn't missed a place in four tries at this distance, winning twice. SEABOW (9) won for the second time in four starts so far this campaign when scoring easily at this circuit and distance on Monday. Draws on the back row this time but he is going well. DYNAMITE DANNI (4) draws better then when runner-up to a runaway winner last week. Include.",
